<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="598" pageId="2" pageNumber="597" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[1406,2613,2901,3256]" pageId="2" pageNumber="597">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1408,1661,3098,3131]" pageId="2" pageNumber="597">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head—body 66-80 mm, tail 50-69 mm, hindfoot 14-17 mm. No specific data are available for body weight. Color of the Chinese Shrew Mole is variable; dorsum is dark brown and venteris dark slate-gray. Snout is long and scaly, and is formed of two tubular nostrils with a groove along the top. Ears extend beyond fur
